fields.name: Drawing Note 1
fields.value: NOTE: APPLY HEAT SHRINK WITH GLUE ON OPEN END OF MANIFOLD. HEAT SHRINK TO BE SQUEEZED TOGETHER IN ORDER TO CLOSE MANIFOLD'S EXIT

fields.name: Instruction
fields.value: PLUG BACKSHELL INTO CONNECTOR AS SHOWN ABOVE. CONNECTOR'S LOCK TO BE POINTING TOWARDS BACKSHELL EXIT.

fields.name: Instruction
fields.value: PLUG BACKSHELL INTO CONNECTOR AS SHOWN ABOVE. CONNECTOR'S LOCK TO BE POINTING OPPOSITE TO BACKSHELL EXIT.

fields.name: Drawing Note 6
fields.value: P-CLAMPS TO BE POINTING UPWARDS AT ALL TIME

fields.name: Specification 2
fields.value: 2. REFER TO DIN76722 TYPE-B (FLRY-B) UNLESS OTHERWISE SPECIFIED.

fields.name: Specification 3
fields.value: 3. CIRCUIT NUMBER TO BE PRINTED ON THE WIRES IN 40 MM INTERVALS.

fields.name: Specification 4
fields.value: 4. BREAKOUTS TO BE MADE WITH SUITABLE MANIFOLDS UNLESS OTHERWISE SPECIFIED IN CASE NO SUITABLE MANIFOLDS ARE AVAILABLE, BREAKOUTS TO BE TAPED WITH TEXTILE TAPE.

fields.name: Specification 5
fields.value: 5. ALL UNUSED CAVITIES OF WATERPROOF CONNECTORS MUST BE PLUGGED WITH CAVITIY PLUGS.

fields.name: Specification 6
fields.value: 6. ALL BREAKOUTS TO BE ORIENTED LIKE DRAWN.

fields.name: Specification 7
fields.value: 7. FOR ALL DOUBLE HEAD TIE BANDS, LOOP AND ATTACH ONE END ONLY TO HARNESS AND LEAVE OTHER END OPEN

fields.name: Specification 8
fields.value: 8. EQUIVALENT TERMINAL, SEAL OR BACKSHELL PART NUMBER BY THE SAME MANUFACTURER MAY BE SUBSTITUTED.

fields.name: Specification 9
fields.value: 9. SPLICE LOCATIONS ARE REFERENCE ONLY; EXCEPT FOR CAN DATA AND TWISTED PAIR CIRCUIT AS APPLICABLE.

fields.name: Specification 10
fields.value: 10. ALL TWISTED PAIRS, TRIPLE OR QUAD CABLES SHOULD HAVE MINIMUM ONE TWIST PER 25 MM AS APPLICABLE.

fields.name: Specification 11
fields.value: 11. SPACING BETWEEN ADJACENT SPLICES 25 MM MINIMUM.

fields.name: Specification 12
fields.value: 12. SPLICES MUST BE INSULATED WITH HOT MELT HEAT SHRINK.

fields.name: Specification 13
fields.value: 13. OVERLAP CONDUIT TO BE SELECTED: SCHLEMMER TWIN UNLESS OTHERWISE APPROVED BY ENGINEERING.

fields.name: Specification 14
fields.value: 14. FOR NON-SLIT CONDUIT TO BE USED: SCHLEMMER POLYFLEX UFW PP MOD UNLESS OTHERWISE SPECIFIED.

fields.name: Specification 15
fields.value: 15. CONDUITS TO BE CUT ON THE CREST.

fields.name: Specification 16
fields.value: 16. ALL OPEN CONDUIT END TO BE TEXTILE SPOT TAPED.

fields.name: Specification 17
fields.value: 17. APPLY HEAT SHRINK W/O GLUE OVER CONNECTOR END AND CONDUIT WHERE APPLICABLE.

fields.name: Specification 18
fields.value: 18. ATTACH FIR TREE TO MANIFOLD AS SHOWN. TAPE MANIFOLD SURFACE IF REQUIRED.

fields.name: Specification 19
fields.value: 19. APPLY NON-SLIT CONDUIT FOR BRANCHES COMING OUT OF MANIFOLD: 57M13339.

fields.name: Specification 20
fields.value: 20. WIRE FLR2X EXCHANGED AGAINST P3S WIRE ACCORDING TO SAME ISO6722 T3 REQUIREMENTS AS CONFIRMED PER JDZW PF.

fields.name: Specification 21
fields.value: 21. ADD LABEL BEHIND EVERY CONNECTOR WITH DESIGNATION.

fields.name: Specification 22
fields.value: 22. PLACE P-CLAMPS WITH ITS ROUND SIDE POINTING UPWARDS. IN A WAY THAT THE FLAT SIDE LAYS ON THE BOARD.
